# Quantum Kapital morning-sweep cron entry.
#
# 1. Substitute <repo> and <account> below.
# 2. Append the (uncommented) line to your crontab via `crontab -e`.
# 3. Build the MCP server binary first:
#       cd <repo>/src-tauri && cargo build --release --bin mcp-server
# 4. Make sure the Tauri desktop app is running before 07:00 ET (Phase 9
#    daemon will lift this requirement).
#
# Schedule: 07:00 America/New_York, Mon-Fri. The dev script also early-exits
# on US market holidays so it is safe to fire 5 days a week regardless.
#
# IMPORTANT: cron runs in the local server timezone, not necessarily ET. If
# your host is on UTC, adjust the minute/hour fields accordingly. Example:
#   - America/New_York 07:00 EST  = UTC 12:00
#   - America/New_York 07:00 EDT  = UTC 11:00
# Easiest: run on a host set to America/New_York, then the spec below is
# unambiguous. Otherwise use systemd timers (which support TZ=America/New_York
# directly) — see the README.

# m  h  dom mon dow  command
  0  7  *   *   1-5  /home/<account>/<repo>/loop/morning_sweep_dev.sh >> /home/<account>/<repo>/loop/morning_sweep.log 2>&1
